h3. Current Situation
* Currently, when a user is deleted they're listed as *Name (Unlicensed)*;

h3. Suggestions
* In some cases it would be useful for Admins to rename these deleted users;
* Provide the ability for Admins to transfer page's ownership to another user

h3. Issue Summary
On Confluence pages, we are not able to choose the thumbnail for the uploaded videos.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Edit/create a page;
 # Insert a video to the page;
 # Click on the video and check the options;
 # Publish page;

h3. Expected Results
You're able to choose the thumbnail for the video on the options;

h3. Actual Results
The thumbnail is randomly chosen and you're not able to select a new one.

h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
While using the *Navigation Maps* macro, it provides us with an option to set the cells' width and height. 
These fields say it is optional to insert or not the *px* at the end of the pixel size, but it happens that if we opt to use it, the cells won't change their height and/or width.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add the label "_banana_" on an existing page;
# Create a new page
# Insert the *Navigation Maps* macro;
# In the macro settings set the field *Label* with "_banana_";
# In the width field set it to 200;
# In the height field set it to 400;
# Click over the preview button to see how the cells will be;
# Change the width or height to 200/400 and add *px* in the end;
# Preview the cells one more time.

h3. Expected Results
Nothing is changed, as we have just inserted the optional information.

h3. Actual Results
The cell gets back to its default size.

*Notes*
* Even saving it and publishing the page, the cells don't get the size we set.

h3. Workaround
Don't use the px in the end of the width/height size.

h3. Issue Summary
The PDF macro is not showing the PDF on the Confluence APP, it shows a blank space where it should be the PDF macro.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create/Edit a page with the new editor;
 # Upload a PDF file on the page;
 # Insert the  PDF macro and save;
 # Publish the page;
 # Access the Confluence APP for android or iOS;
 # Access the page published;


h3. Expected Results
You're able to see the PDF on your Confluence APP for android or iOS.
h3. Actual Results
It shows the PDF (where is the PDF macro) as blank.

Notes: 
* It returns no errors.
* It is visible on desktop, but does not work on the mobile browser (View ViewPDF on desktop error);


h3. Workaround
There is no workaround at the moment.
